that is actually usable.

Thought for 6s
# 1) Set variables
APPID=1282100
SESSION_ID=remnant2__ward13_idle__20260405_120000
SESSION_DIR="$PWD/analysis/games/remnant2/sessions/${SESSION_ID}"
mkdir -p "$SESSION_DIR/notes"
# 2) Record .foz state BEFORE launching the game
find ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
     ~/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
     -path '*/fozpipelinesv6/*.foz' -type f \
     -printf '%TY-%Tm-%Td %TH:%TM:%TS %s %p\n' 2>/dev/null | sort \
     > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_before.txt"
# 3) Put this in Steam launch options for the game
ENABLE_VULKAN_RENDERDOC_CAPTURE=1 %command%

Use:

Open Steam.
Right click the game → Properties.
In Launch Options, paste:
ENABLE_VULKAN_RENDERDOC_CAPTURE=1 %command%

This is the Proton/Vulkan RenderDoc capture path.

# 4) Start RenderDoc
qrenderdoc

Use:

Leave RenderDoc open.
Launch the game from Steam.
Enter the exact scene.
In RenderDoc: File → Attach to Running Instance.
Select the Proton game process, usually wine-preloader or wine64-preloader.
Press the capture button in RenderDoc when the scene is exactly where you want it.
# 5) Save the capture manually from RenderDoc
# save it as something like:
# /absolute/path/to/frame.rdc
#
# also save one screenshot manually as:
# /absolute/path/to/frame.png

Use:

After capture, open the captured frame in RenderDoc.
Save the .rdc.
Export at least one screenshot.
# 6) Record .foz state AFTER the capture, same run window
find ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
     ~/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
     -path '*/fozpipelinesv6/*.foz' -type f \
     -printf '%TY-%Tm-%Td %TH:%TM:%TS %s %p\n' 2>/dev/null | sort \
     > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_after.txt"
# 7) Diff before vs after to identify the .foz changed by this run
diff -u "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_before.txt" "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_after.txt" \
  > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_diff.txt" || true

Use:

Open foz_diff.txt.
Identify the .foz file whose timestamp and/or size changed during this same run window.
That is the .foz to register for the same capture session.

Fossilize .foz is pipeline/object state serialization, not full scene replay, so you sync it by same run window and changed cache file, not by visual frame extraction.

# 8) Copy the selected .foz into your session folder
cp /absolute/path/to/steamapp_pipeline_cache.foz \
   "${SESSION_DIR}/track_b_pipeline_mining/"
# 9) Optional: verify file hash
sha256sum "${SESSION_DIR}/track_b_pipeline_mining/steamapp_pipeline_cache.foz"
sha256sum /absolute/path/to/frame.rdc
# 10) If your pipeline scripts already exist, register the RenderDoc capture
python3 -m scripts.analysis_pipeline.track_a.register_capture \
  --session "${SESSION_ID}" \
  --rdc /absolute/path/to/frame.rdc \
  --screenshot /absolute/path/to/frame.png
# 11) Register the .foz from the same run window
python3 -m scripts.analysis_pipeline.track_b.register_foz \
  --session "${SESSION_ID}" \
  --foz /absolute/path/to/steamapp_pipeline_cache.foz
# 12) Mine the .foz
python3 -m scripts.analysis_pipeline.track_b.mine_pipelines \
  --session "${SESSION_ID}"
# 13) Correlate later
python3 -m scripts.analysis_pipeline.track_c.correlate_session \
  --session "${SESSION_ID}" \
  --run-legacy-extract

Minimal usage flow:

APPID=1282100
SESSION_ID=remnant2__ward13_idle__20260405_120000
SESSION_DIR="$PWD/analysis/games/remnant2/sessions/${SESSION_ID}"
mkdir -p "$SESSION_DIR/notes"

find ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} ~/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
  -path '*/fozpipelinesv6/*.foz' -type f -printf '%TY-%Tm-%Td %TH:%TM:%TS %s %p\n' 2>/dev/null | sort \
  > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_before.txt"

qrenderdoc
# Steam launch options:
# ENABLE_VULKAN_RENDERDOC_CAPTURE=1 %command%
# Launch game from Steam, go to scene, attach in RenderDoc to wine-preloader/wine64-preloader, capture, save frame.rdc + frame.png

find ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} ~/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/shadercache/${APPID} \
  -path '*/fozpipelinesv6/*.foz' -type f -printf '%TY-%Tm-%Td %TH:%TM:%TS %s %p\n' 2>/dev/null | sort \
  > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_after.txt"

diff -u "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_before.txt" "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_after.txt" \
  > "${SESSION_DIR}/notes/foz_diff.txt" || true

If RenderDoc capture does not work under your desktop/session, a known workaround reported recently is disabling Gamescope WSI for that launch:

ENABLE_GAMESCOPE_WSI=0 ENABLE_VULKAN_RENDERDOC_CAPTURE=1 %command%

That workaround has been reported for recent RenderDoc/Gamescope interactions.